        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 12 at 12:46AM EDT by NWS Binghamton NY</headline>
        <description>At 1245 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Morrisville, or near Hamilton, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Oneida, Eaton, Hamilton, Sherrill, Morrisville, Stockbridge, Augusta,
Nelson, Waterville, and Vernon.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
